
# ğŸš€ Kubernetes Multi-Node Cluster Setup using `kubeadm` on Ubuntu 24.04

This guide helps you set up a **multi-node Kubernetes cluster** using `kubeadm`, `containerd`, and **Ubuntu 24.04**.

## ğŸ§± Architecture

| Role   | Description        | Nodes       |
|--------|--------------------|-------------|
| Master | Control Plane Node | 1 node      |
| Worker | App/Pod Nodes      | 1+ nodes    |

---

## ğŸ“‹ Overview of Steps

| Step | Description                         | Applies To       |
|------|-------------------------------------|------------------|
| 1ï¸âƒ£   | System prerequisites                | All nodes        |
| 2ï¸âƒ£   | Install and configure containerd    | All nodes        |
| 3ï¸âƒ£   | Install Kubernetes tools            | All nodes        |
| 4ï¸âƒ£   | Initialize Kubernetes cluster       | Master node      |
| 5ï¸âƒ£   | Install Pod Network (Flannel)       | Master node      |
| 6ï¸âƒ£   | Join workers to the cluster         | Worker nodes     |
| 7ï¸âƒ£   | Verify cluster status               | Master node      |

---

## 1ï¸âƒ£ System Prerequisites (All Nodes)

### ğŸš« Disable Swap
```bash
sudo swapoff -a
sudo sed -i '/ swap / s/^/#/' /etc/fstab
````

### ğŸ§© Load Kernel Modules

```bash
sudo modprobe overlay
sudo modprobe br_netfilter

sudo tee /etc/modules-load.d/k8s.conf <<EOF
overlay
br_netfilter
EOF
```

### ğŸ”§ Configure Sysctl

```bash
sudo tee /etc/sysctl.d/k8s.conf <<EOF
net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-ip6tables = 1
net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-iptables = 1
net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1
EOF

sudo sysctl --system
```

---

## 2ï¸âƒ£ Install containerd (All Nodes)

### ğŸ“¦ Install containerd

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y containerd
```

### âš™ï¸ Configure containerd

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /etc/containerd
containerd config default | sudo tee /etc/containerd/config.toml

# Enable systemd cgroup driver
sudo sed -i 's/SystemdCgroup = false/SystemdCgroup = true/' /etc/containerd/config.toml

sudo systemctl restart containerd
sudo systemctl enable containerd
```

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ Install Kubernetes Tools (All Nodes)

### ğŸ“¥ Add Kubernetes Repository

```bash
sudo apt install -y apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl gpg

curl -fsSL https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.29/deb/Release.key | \
  sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg

echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/kubernetes-apt-keyring.gpg] https://pkgs.k8s.io/core:/stable:/v1.29/deb/ /" \
  | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/kubernetes.list
```

### ğŸš€ Install kubeadm, kubelet, kubectl

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y kubelet kubeadm kubectl
sudo apt-mark hold kubelet kubeadm kubectl
```

---

## 4ï¸âƒ£ Initialize Cluster (Master Node Only)

### ğŸ§­ Initialize

```bash
sudo kubeadm init --pod-network-cidr=10.244.0.0/16
```

### ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ’» Set up kubectl for the master

```bash
mkdir -p $HOME/.kube
sudo cp /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf $HOME/.kube/config
sudo chown $(id -u):$(id -g) $HOME/.kube/config
```

---

## 5ï¸âƒ£ Install Pod Network (Flannel) ğŸŒ

```bash
kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/coreos/flannel/master/Documentation/kube-flannel.yml
```

---

## 6ï¸âƒ£ Join Worker Nodes ğŸ”—

Run on each **worker node**, using the join command from the master:

```bash
kubeadm join <MASTER-IP>:6443 --token <TOKEN> --discovery-token-ca-cert-hash sha256:<HASH>
```

> Replace `<MASTER-IP>`, `<TOKEN>`, and `<HASH>` with actual values from:
>
> ```bash
> kubeadm token create --print-join-command
> ```

---

## 7ï¸âƒ£ Verify the Cluster âœ…

```bash
kubectl get nodes
```

Expected:

```
NAME         STATUS   ROLES           AGE   VERSION
master       Ready    control-plane   5m    v1.29.x
worker-1     Ready    <none>          2m    v1.29.x
```

